<strong>Distance:</strong> 8.7 km out &amp; back &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Time:</strong> ~3 h 05 min &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Elevation Gain:</strong> 421 m
</div>

<p>This AllTrails favorite follows the scenic Yukawa River corridor between two of Nikko National Park’s most photogenic waterfalls. Starting near the tea houses beside Ryuzu Falls, the path alternates between cedar forest boardwalks and gently climbing dirt tracks that parallel the cascading river toward Lake Yunoko.</p>

<p>Expect misty viewpoints, seasonal foliage color, and the thunder of water as you crest the final stairs beside Yudaki Falls. The moderate ascent rewards you with panoramic views over the marshlands of Senjogahara and easy access to the Yumoto Onsen village for a restorative soak after the hike.</p>

